--><i> are</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> two major sources of power generation in use today and for a long time now.  It is common capitalist practice to make comparisons between the top competitors or leaders in a given area.  Comparing solar or wind power which amounts to trivial levels of actual power being utilized against the major providers such as coal or nuclear would be like comparing a small time player to a major corporation.<br>
<br>
This doesn't mean that wind and solar won't be major players in the energy market someday... but wishing doesn't make it so.<br>
